    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-04-04T13:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-04-04T13:00:00-05:00" n="483"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d483">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">339.115 General Motors Export Co./⅙:
                    Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in the Dominican Republic</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Schoenfeld</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Santo Domingo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-04-04T13:00:00-05:00"
                            >April 4, 1935—1 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 3:45 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>11. I am informed that Mr. Amadeo Barletta honorary Italian Consul in Santo
                    Domingo and president of Santo Domingo Motors Company and of Dominican Tobacco
                    Company respectively was arrested on his arrival at San Pedro de Macoris by air
                    from San Juan this morning and is detained in the fortress here. I understand
                    that clerk of the Italian Consulate has telegraphed the Italian Minister at
                    Habana but there is some question whether this telegram which was sent in clear
                    was permitted to go out.</p>
                <p>See enclosures to my personal letters of March 14 and March 16<note n="1"
                        xml:id="d483fn1">Not found in Department files.</note> to the Chief of
                    Division of Latin American Affairs. American citizens including officers of
                    General Motors Export Company of New York and Penn Tobacco Company of
                    Wilkes-Barre, Pennsylvania are understood to have substantial stock interest in
                    companies mentioned of which Barletta is president. No official information is
                    available as to reasons for detention of the Consul nor has it been announced
                    whether his exequatur has been canceled. Suggest that Department cause Italian
                    Legation at Havana to be advised if no objection to so doing is seen.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Schoenfeld</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
